+# Unreal Pixel Perfect 2D Client Studio Proof Checklist
+
+## Client Goal
+
+Turn the existing Unreal Paper2D pixel-perfect sample into a small proof slice that makes the project's visual-quality policy more explicit and harder to regress.
+
+## Scope Lock
+
+- Keep the original Paper2D character, map, sprites, materials, and project settings.
+- Improve the viewport-level pixel-perfect presentation policy only.
+- Preserve the existing game mode, character movement, input bindings, and content assets.
+- Do not add new art, UMG screens, Niagara effects, or broad gameplay systems.
+
+## Formal Art Direction
+
+- Keep the existing pixel-art / Paper2D visual identity.
+- Treat crisp sprite rendering as the primary art-direction requirement.
+- Preserve the no-post-processing policy so pixel colors and sprite edges remain intentional.
+- Avoid UI or debug overlays in this proof slice.
+
+## Architecture Boundary
+
+- `SampleGameViewportClient` owns viewport show flag policy.
+- `SampleCharacter` owns movement, animation selection, and facing direction.
+- `SampleGameMode` owns default pawn selection only.
+- `DefaultEngine.ini` owns the viewport client registration.
+- Content assets remain data and presentation assets, not proof logic.
+
+## QA Checklist
+
+| Check | Expected |
+|---|---|
+| Viewport client registered | `DefaultEngine.ini` points to `SampleGameViewportClient`. |
+| Pixel-perfect policy | `ApplyPixelPerfectShowFlags()` disables post processing. |
+| Runtime persistence | `Draw()` reapplies the policy before frame rendering. |
+| Character boundary | Character code does not own viewport show flags. |
+| Game mode boundary | Game mode does not own visual render policy. |
+| Paper2D plugin | `Sample.uproject` keeps Paper2D enabled. |
+
+## Acceptance Criteria
+
+- Pixel-perfect visual policy is explicit and isolated.
+- Gameplay classes do not own render policy.
+- Static smoke passes.
+- Unreal editor compile and PIE are required before final client acceptance.
+
+## Ruthless Playtester Note
+
+This proof strengthens the sample's visual discipline, but it still has no player-facing goal, HUD, or progression. It proves Unreal presentation boundaries, not a complete game loop.
diff --git a/Proof/static_smoke.mjs b/Proof/static_smoke.mjs
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..cd1a6a1
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Proof/static_smoke.mjs
@@ -0,0 +1,77 @@
+import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
+import { join, resolve } from 'node:path';
+
+const projectRoot = resolve(process.cwd());
+const failures = [];
+
+function assert(condition, message) {
+  if (!condition) {
+    failures.push(message);
+  }
+}
+
+function read(relativePath) {
+  return readFileSync(join(projectRoot, relativePath), 'utf8');
+}
+
+const requiredFiles = [
+  'README.md',
+  'LICENSE',
+  'Sample.uproject',
+  'Config/DefaultEngine.ini',
+  'Source/Sample/SampleGameViewportClient.h',
+  'Source/Sample/SampleGameViewportClient.cpp',
+  'Source/Sample/SampleCharacter.cpp',
+  'Source/Sample/SampleGameMode.cpp',
+  'Proof/client_studio_acceptance.md'
+];
+
+for (const file of requiredFiles) {
+  assert(existsSync(join(projectRoot, file)), `Missing ${file}`);
+}
+
+const readme = read('README.md');
+const license = read('LICENSE');
+const project = read('Sample.uproject');
+const engineConfig = read('Config/DefaultEngine.ini');
+const viewportHeader = read('Source/Sample/SampleGameViewportClient.h');
+const viewportSource = read('Source/Sample/SampleGameViewportClient.cpp');
+const characterSource = read('Source/Sample/SampleCharacter.cpp');
+const gameModeSource = read('Source/Sample/SampleGameMode.cpp');
+const checklist = read('Proof/client_studio_acceptance.md');
+
+assert(readme.includes('pixel perfect 2D game in Unreal Engine 5 with Paper2D'), 'README should identify the Unreal Paper2D visual target');
+assert(readme.includes('EngineShowFlags.PostProcessing'), 'README should document the post-processing risk');
+assert(license.includes('MIT License'), 'Project should keep MIT license evidence');
+assert(project.includes('"EngineAssociation": "5.2"'), 'Project should record the Unreal engine association');
+assert(project.includes('"Name": "Paper2D"'), 'Project should keep the Paper2D plugin enabled');
+assert(engineConfig.includes('GameViewportClientClassName=/Script/Sample.SampleGameViewportClient'), 'DefaultEngine should register the custom viewport client');
+assert(viewportHeader.includes('void Draw(FViewport* InViewport, FCanvas* SceneCanvas) override;'), 'Viewport client should override Draw');
+assert(viewportHeader.includes('void ApplyPixelPerfectShowFlags();'), 'Viewport client should isolate pixel-perfect show flags');
+assert(viewportSource.includes('ApplyPixelPerfectShowFlags();'), 'Viewport source should call the pixel-perfect policy');
+assert(viewportSource.includes('Super::Draw(InViewport, SceneCanvas);'), 'Viewport source should preserve the engine draw path');
+assert(viewportSource.includes('EngineShowFlags.PostProcessing = 0;'), 'Viewport policy should disable post processing');
+assert(!characterSource.includes('EngineShowFlags'), 'Character should not own render show flags');
+assert(!gameModeSource.includes('EngineShowFlags'), 'GameMode should not own render show flags');
+assert(checklist.includes('Formal Art Direction'), 'Checklist should document the art direction gate');
+assert(checklist.includes('Architecture Boundary'), 'Checklist should document architecture boundaries');
+assert(checklist.includes('Unreal editor compile and PIE are required'), 'Checklist should not pretend runtime checks passed');
+
+const lineCounts = {
+  viewportHeader: viewportHeader.split(/\r?\n/).filter(Boolean).length,
+  viewportSource: viewportSource.split(/\r?\n/).filter(Boolean).length,
+  characterSource: characterSource.split(/\r?\n/).filter(Boolean).length,
+  gameModeSource: gameModeSource.split(/\r?\n/).filter(Boolean).length
+};
+
+assert(lineCounts.viewportHeader < 30, `Viewport header should stay small: ${lineCounts.viewportHeader} lines`);
+assert(lineCounts.viewportSource < 35, `Viewport source should stay focused: ${lineCounts.viewportSource} lines`);
+assert(lineCounts.characterSource < 130, `Character source should remain sample-scale: ${lineCounts.characterSource} lines`);
+assert(lineCounts.gameModeSource < 20, `GameMode source should remain focused: ${lineCounts.gameModeSource} lines`);
+
+if (failures.length > 0) {
+  console.error(failures.map((failure) => `[FAIL] ${failure}`).join('\n'));
+  process.exit(1);
+}
+
+console.log('unreal pixelperfect2d proof static smoke: passed');
